\Omega \subseteq \mathbb{R}^N
d(x):=\text{dist} (x,\partial \Omega) =\inf_{y\in \partial \Omega} |x-y|\;.
\forall x,y \in \Omega
d(x)\geq d(y)
\forall \varepsilon >0
\exists z \in \partial \Omega
d(y)+\varepsilon > |y-z|
|x-z| \geq d(x)
0 \leq d(x)-d(y) \leq |x-z| - |y-z| +\varepsilon \leq |x-y| + \varepsilon 
\varepsilon
\partial \Omega
\Omega
d_{A}:\mathbb{R}^n\rightarrow \mathbb{R}
d_{A}(x)=\inf_{A}|x-y|
